<div class="c230_123"> 
<div id="v230.123.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H5375 s">. Unto thee lift I up</span><span class="H5869 s"> mine eyes</span><span class="H3427 s">, O thou that dwellest</span><span class="H8064 s"> in the heavens</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.123.2"><span class="H5869 s">Behold, as the eyes</span><span class="H5650 s"> of servants</span><span class="H3027 s"> <i>look</i> unto the hand</span><span class="H113 s"> of their masters</span><span class="H5869 s">, <i>and</i> as the eyes</span><span class="H8198 s"> of a maiden</span><span class="H3027 s"> unto the hand</span><span class="H1404 s"> of her mistress</span><span class="H5869 s">; so our eyes</span><span class="H3068 s"> <i>wait</i> upon the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> our God</span><span class="H2603 s">, until that he have mercy</span> upon us.</div> 
<div id="v230.123.3"><span class="H2603 s">Have mercy</span><span class="H3068 s"> upon us, O LORD</span><span class="H2603 s">, have mercy</span><span class="H7227 s"> upon us: for we are exceedingly</span><span class="H7646 s"> filled</span><span class="H937 s"> with contempt</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.123.4"><span class="H5315 s">Our soul</span><span class="H7227 s"> is exceedingly</span><span class="H7646 s"> filled</span><span class="H3933 s"> with the scorning</span><span class="H7600 s"> of those that are at ease</span><span class="H937 s">, <i>and</i> with the contempt</span><span class="H3238 s"> of the proud</span><span class="H1343 s"> †</span><span class="H1349 s"> †</span>.</div></div> 
